data.text:
The Icelandic culinary team received the gold medal at the culinary world cup in Luxemburg last night. The team had six hours to prepare a three-course meal for judges and 110 guests. In a press announcement from team manger Hafliði Halldórson the win confirms the Icelandic culinary team as very strong. "We've put emphasis on using Icelandic ingredients such as lamb, cod, lobster, skyr and Icelandic vegetables."

The winning meal consisted of a starter of Icelandic cod and pan-fried lobster with an apple and artichoke salad, quinoa and a dill-mustard sauce, an entrée of grilled Icelandic lamb with celeriac, a potato and mushroom croquette, glazed carrots and onion and a thyme-mushroom sauce. The dessert was a strawberry and yoghurt mousse with dark chocolate and skyr, an almond-caramel cake, whipped sour cream and strawberries.
